  "text": "Most important, amnion membrane provides a rich source of factors which enhance angiogenesis; these include angiogenin, fibroblast growth factor and vascular endothelial growth factor, to name a few.These factors enhance proliferation of endothelial cells and boost the angiogenesis with new vessel formation [CITATION_1] . Evidence substantiates that amnion membrane also plays a crucial role in recruitment of mesenchymal progenitor cells and help in accelerating wound healing. Finally, unlike the other membranes used in GTR that have reported adverse immune response, this membrane is completely safe [CITATION_2] .",
